=== Noun ===
'''{{PAGENAME}}''' ([[おんよみ]], ''[[on'yomi]]'')

# The [[reading]] (''yomi'') (i.e. [[pronunciation]]) of a Japanese word written in [[kanji]] that is roughly based on the Chinese pronunciation of the kanji characters at the time the word was introduced to Japan.  
#: As words written in kanji were brought to Japan at different times rather than all at once, ''on'yomi'' are categorized as ''[[goon]]'' ([[呉音]], [[ごおん]]), ''[[kan'on]]'' ([[漢音]], [[かんおん]]), and ''[[tōon]]'' ([[唐音]], [[とうおん]]).  The same kanji may be used to mean different things depending on the reading, such as [[利益]] which means "[[profit]]" when read with the ''kan'on'' pronunciation [[りえき]], and means "[[Buddhist]] [[blessing]] or [[salvation]]" when read with the ''goon'' pronunciation [[りやく]].  
#: ''On'yomi'' loosely corresponds to ''[[kango]]'' ([[漢語]], [[かんご]]), with ''on'yomi'' indicating the reading and ''kango'' indicating the actual word itself.  

